@afchung Thanks.
@yunseong The Travis CI build failed. Did you take a look? 

Adding @johnyangk as well. What happens when there is an exception while executing `VortexFunction`? How does Vortex handle this case? I'm guessing `VortexFuture` should have a way to tell it.

@bgchun 

We have `TOutput call(TInput input) throws Exception` in `VortexFunction`. This means that user code can throw an exception inside the call. The exception is caught in the Evaluator and forwarded to Driver, same as how the result is forwarded.

You are right. The exception is surfaced to the user via `TOutput get() throws InterruptedException, ExecutionException` in `VortexFuture` as an `ExecutionException`.
